Listen, I feel like I have been giving out a bunch of 5’s recently, but I don’t give a damn this movie destroyed me. It was the best depiction of toxic masculinity, brotherly love, and everything in between that I have seen put to film in a hit minute. I love what this movie says about men. I love what this movie says about legacy. I love what this movie says about parenting. I love what this movie says about breaking generational curses.
This movie is simultaneously so ahead of its time while also being such a product of its time; it’s kinda wild if you think about it
